Cell["\<\
The Bravais-Spearman correlation coefficient is -0.43, and the Spearman \
correlation coefficient is -0.39. They indicate that we have a weak-moderate \
negative association (decreasing temperature for increasing delivery time). \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.947139576689361*^9, 
  3.947139662201713*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"15c87336-14ad-4e12-99f1-\
1150435f678f"],

Cell["\<\
Solution to (e):
(e) Use methods of your choice to explore the relationship between \
temperature and driver, operator, number of ordered pizzas and bill. Is it \
clear which of the variables influence the pizza temperature?
Association between temperature and driver:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.947139827852385*^9, 3.947139831740059*^9}, {
